Help Type: command
Command: wikigraph <archive-uri>/chapter list

chapter list

Purpose:
  List every chapter and its stored artifact readiness.

Usage:
  wikigraph <archive-uri>/chapter list [--all] [--limit <n>] [--cursor <token>] [--json|--jsonl] [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]

Output shape:
  wkg://chapter/<id>  <title-or-[untitled]>  source:<ready|missing> reading-graph:<ready|missing> reading-summary:<ready|missing> knowledge-graph:<ready|missing>

  With `--jsonl`, each chapter is one JSON object with `uri`, `title`, and `state`.

Behavior:
  - Includes sourced, generated, and unfinished chapters.
  - Use `--all --jsonl` for grep/jq-style readiness checks across every chapter.
  - With `--all`, `--limit` controls page size. Avoid `--all` without `--jsonl` for large results.
  - Chapter ids are encoded in the returned `wkg://chapter/<id>` URIs.
  - Does not call an LLM provider.
  - Does not mutate chapter content or summaries.

Use this before mutation:
  Discover ids and missing generated artifacts with:
    wikigraph <archive-uri>/chapter list --all --jsonl
    wikigraph <archive-uri>/chapter list --all --jsonl | jq 'select(.state["knowledge-graph"] == "missing")'

See also:
